1
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:38,200
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

2
00:00:38,333 --> 00:00:40,133
<i>Only the patient's family
is allowed here.</i>

3
00:00:40,267 --> 00:00:42,033
<i>You have no right to my husband.</i>

4
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:43,100
<i> Leave now!</i>

5
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:45,267
<i>I'll try to get news about Dad.</i>

6
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:46,333
<i> Thank you, Dear.</i>

7
00:00:46,467 --> 00:00:47,400
<i> Why, Mom?</i>

8
00:00:47,533 --> 00:00:48,633
<i> I just missed you.</i>

9
00:00:48,767 --> 00:00:50,300
<i> I missed you, too.</i>

10
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:52,067
<i> Especially Dad.</i>

11
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:53,800
<i> I've forgiven him.</i>

12
00:00:53,933 --> 00:00:55,433
<i> Now you see what could happen?</i>

13
00:00:55,567 --> 00:00:58,067
<i>They could team up
to take your dad away.</i>

14
00:00:58,200 --> 00:01:00,600
<i>Don't let your dad
go back to them.</i>

15
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:01,767
<i> We won't let that happen.</i>

16
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:04,033
<i> You have to see your father.</i>

17
00:01:04,167 --> 00:01:05,133
<i> Not now...</i>

18
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:07,600
<i>Not when your sister
finally wants</i>

19
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:08,967
<i> to make peace with him.</i>

20
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:10,333
<i> I'm sorry, Joel.</i>

21
00:01:10,467 --> 00:01:12,833
<i>Sorry, you keep getting in
trouble because of me.</i>

22
00:01:12,967 --> 00:01:18,200
<i>Thank you, not for saving me,
but for being my friend.</i>

23
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:19,633
<i>Mom's just trying
to stay strong.</i>

24
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:21,733
<i>She's hiding her fear and worry.</i>

25
00:01:21,867 --> 00:01:24,300
<i> Please don't take Manuel away.</i>

26
00:01:24,433 --> 00:01:28,767
<i>I want him to feel
what it is to be loved</i>

27
00:01:28,900 --> 00:01:33,067
<i>by Jeffrey, Andrea, and Coleen.</i>

28
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:36,733
<i> Please save him.</i>

29
00:01:44,567 --> 00:01:45,767
Dr. Richard...

30
00:01:45,900 --> 00:01:46,733
yes.

31
00:01:46,867 --> 00:01:49,267
- Hazel.
- Any news, Doctor?

32
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,867
The surgery was a success.

33
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,600
- Manuel will be fine.
- Oh, thank you.

34
00:01:52,733 --> 00:01:53,833
So, here's what happened.

35
00:01:53,967 --> 00:01:55,867
Manuel had a lung laceration

36
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:57,867
caused by a rib fracture.

37
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:00,100
We stitched it up
and inserted a CTT,

38
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:01,300
or chest tube,

39
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:03,967
So, no more blood and air
within the lungs

40
00:02:04,100 --> 00:02:05,267
that should not be there.

41
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,500
Okay?

42
00:02:06,633 --> 00:02:11,167
For the heart, no major vessels
or arteries are damaged.

43
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:13,433
So, no need to worry about that.

44
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:16,567
His rib fractures, plural,

45
00:02:16,700 --> 00:02:18,400
fractures, there are a lot.

46
00:02:18,533 --> 00:02:22,867
But it's not that extensive
so we won't need to touch them.

47
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,267
Just limitation of movement.

48
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:25,400
Just don't make him move.

49
00:02:25,533 --> 00:02:26,933
That would heal.

50
00:02:27,067 --> 00:02:28,533
Okay?

51
00:02:28,667 --> 00:02:30,600
- Thank you so much, Doc.
- Oh.

52
00:02:30,733 --> 00:02:31,767
- It's okay.
- Sorry.

53
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,300
No, it's okay, it's okay.

54
00:02:33,433 --> 00:02:35,233
It's fine, it's fine.
It's okay.

55
00:02:35,367 --> 00:02:36,767
So, for Manuel, here's the plan.

56
00:02:36,900 --> 00:02:43,700
We'll keep him here
for post-stabilization.

57
00:02:43,833 --> 00:02:45,900
Then after that,
we'll send him to the ICU.

58
00:02:46,033 --> 00:02:48,833
Once he's in the ICU,
you can go visit him.

59
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:49,933
Okay?

60
00:02:50,067 --> 00:02:52,200
I understand, Doc.
Thank you so much again

61
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:54,600
- No problem, okay, hold on.
- Thank you.

62
00:02:54,733 --> 00:02:55,833
Friend!

63
00:02:56,967 --> 00:02:58,700
Sweetheart, did you hear that?

64
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:01,133
Your daddy's so alive,
He survived the surger

65
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,433
Wait, stay here for now.

66
00:03:08,567 --> 00:03:11,800
I'll have the room prepared
where Manuel will be moved to

67
00:03:11,933 --> 00:03:13,067
after the ICU.

68
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:18,133
- Just stay here for now, okay?
- Yes, Mom.

69
00:03:21,233 --> 00:03:22,333
Jessica.

70
00:03:22,467 --> 00:03:23,700
Jessica, how's Dad?

71
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:26,200
Is he okay now?

72
00:03:28,367 --> 00:03:31,633
Is he safe?

73
00:03:34,467 --> 00:03:35,367
Hello?

74
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,200
Mr. Wilson?

75
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:40,167
This is Hazel Cruz,
wife of Manuel Cruz.

76
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,300
I need your help.

77
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:48,100
Okay.

78
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:52,967
Thank you so much, Mr. Wilson.

79
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:54,367
I really appreciate it.

80
00:03:56,300 --> 00:03:59,367
I'm ashamed but I have no one
else to run to.

81
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:01,267
Thank you so much.

82
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,900
Please say hi to Mrs. Wilson.

83
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:05,200
Okay, bye.

84
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:09,867
Success!

85
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:15,833
What's that, friend?

86
00:04:15,967 --> 00:04:18,600
Don't tell me you're planning
to milk the Wilsons for money?

87
00:04:19,667 --> 00:04:21,167
Well...

88
00:04:21,300 --> 00:04:22,800
why not?

89
00:04:22,933 --> 00:04:25,567
They're loaded,
and I need a lot of money.

90
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,400
So?

91
00:04:27,567 --> 00:04:29,533
Why do you need that much?

92
00:04:30,667 --> 00:04:38,067
Let's just say that I'll need it
for my plan to disappear

93
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,967
with Manuel and Jessica.

94
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:43,167
Hazel, what are you up
to this time?

95
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:46,033
What did the doctor say?

96
00:04:46,967 --> 00:04:48,133
Is Dad okay?

97
00:04:48,800 --> 00:04:50,900
Come on, Jessica.

98
00:04:51,033 --> 00:04:52,333
Please.

99
00:04:52,467 --> 00:04:54,267
I just want to know
how Dad's doing.

100
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,467
Jessica, please,
do it for Mom.

101
00:05:01,633 --> 00:05:02,867
She's worried too.

102
00:05:04,067 --> 00:05:05,900
Won't you stop?

103
00:05:06,033 --> 00:05:06,700
Huh?

104
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:08,400
Can't you understand?

105
00:05:08,533 --> 00:05:10,467
I just want to know
how my father is.

106
00:05:11,467 --> 00:05:13,067
Multiple fractured ribs.

107
00:05:14,167 --> 00:05:15,400
Punctured lungs.

108
00:05:15,533 --> 00:05:17,000
Internal bleeding.

109
00:05:17,133 --> 00:05:18,133
Injuries.

110
00:05:18,267 --> 00:05:20,600
He almost died because of you!

111
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:23,600
What? Is that news
enough for you?

112
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,033
Aren't you ashamed?

113
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:29,833
How will you face Manuel now?

114
00:05:29,967 --> 00:05:31,100
Do you even want him to see

115
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:33,200
the person who nearly
killed him?

116
00:06:12,933 --> 00:06:15,300
There are still so many...

117
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:18,533
machines hooked up to Dad.

118
00:06:19,967 --> 00:06:21,733
Oh...

119
00:06:21,867 --> 00:06:24,133
But is he okay?

120
00:06:24,267 --> 00:06:25,967
Is he safe now?

121
00:06:26,100 --> 00:06:27,767
I don't know...

122
00:06:31,067 --> 00:06:34,200
I only found out they brought
him to the ICU because...

123
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:37,233
I watched outside the OR.

124
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:39,400
What kind of life is this?

125
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:41,167
Do we really have to spy around

126
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:43,133
just to know how Dad's doing?

127
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:44,533
<i> Don't worry.</i>

128
00:06:46,033 --> 00:06:47,467
Hazel can go to war with me
if she wants.

129
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,467
I won't stop.

130
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:55,767
I won't give up until
I get close to Dad.

131
00:06:55,900 --> 00:06:58,733
Andrea, don't waste your time
on that woman.

132
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:00,267
Just leave.

133
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:01,733
<i>Let's just wait for Dad
to wake up.</i>

134
00:07:01,867 --> 00:07:03,567
<i> Mom's right.</i>

135
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:05,900
<i>When he wakes up, the first
people he'll look for are us.</i>

136
00:07:06,033 --> 00:07:07,133
<i> He'll come to us himself.</i>

137
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:10,700
Jessica and Hazel
have already left.

138
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:16,667
Sis, can we just do
a video call?

139
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:19,267
Please show Dad to us.

140
00:07:19,400 --> 00:07:21,033
<i>Alright.
Just a second, okay?</i>

141
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:51,433
I want...

142
00:07:51,567 --> 00:07:53,633
I want to be near Dad.

143
00:07:56,933 --> 00:07:58,733
I want to hug him.

144
00:08:01,767 --> 00:08:03,433
It's been so long.

145
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:08,267
I can't even remember what it
feels like to hold him.

146
00:08:12,400 --> 00:08:14,800
I just want to hug him.

147
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:16,633
<i> Dear...</i>

148
00:08:16,767 --> 00:08:19,333
<i> it's only a short contract...</i>

149
00:08:19,467 --> 00:08:22,033
<i>just two years,
It'll pass quickly.</i>

150
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,567
<i>Once I've saved enough,
I'll come home right away.</i>

151
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:30,200
<i> Dad! Dad!</i>

152
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:38,033
<i>Andrea, that's enough,
stop crying.</i>

153
00:08:38,167 --> 00:08:39,200
<i> Come on,</i>

154
00:08:39,333 --> 00:08:42,000
<i>you'll only make yourself sick,
hush now, it's okay.</i>

155
00:08:43,133 --> 00:08:44,067
<i> That's enough.</i>

156
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,667
<i> I promise I'll come back soon.</i>

157
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,567
Andrea!

158
00:09:15,567 --> 00:09:17,400
- Sis!
- Andrea!

159
00:09:17,533 --> 00:09:18,700
Didn't I tell you...

160
00:09:18,833 --> 00:09:19,767
Ouch!

161
00:09:19,900 --> 00:09:20,900
You're so stubborn!

162
00:09:21,033 --> 00:09:23,100
That Hazel's fighting
Andrea again?

163
00:09:23,233 --> 00:09:25,433
- Let go of my sister!
- Let go of me!

164
00:09:25,567 --> 00:09:26,800
Let go?

165
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,400
Ouch!

166
00:09:28,567 --> 00:09:30,600
- She's hurting Andrea!
- Didn't I tell you...

167
00:09:30,733 --> 00:09:33,233
- Let go of me!
- No! I told you,

168
00:09:33,367 --> 00:09:34,467
you're not supposed to be here!

169
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:37,067
Why are you so hardheaded?
Huh? So stubborn!

170
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:38,800
<i> Mom, stop it!</i>

171
00:09:41,533 --> 00:09:42,633
Mom, where are you going?

172
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:43,967
Mom!

173
00:09:51,267 --> 00:09:52,233
Let go of me, Hazel!

174
00:09:52,367 --> 00:09:54,033
You're not scared of me, huh?

175
00:09:54,167 --> 00:09:55,767
Fine, we'll see about that....

176
00:09:55,900 --> 00:09:57,700
- Mommy!
- So you'd rather get hurt?

177
00:09:57,833 --> 00:09:59,800
- Oh!
- Yes!

178
00:09:59,933 --> 00:10:03,300
- Mommy! Andrea!
- You've only seen my fangs.

179
00:10:03,467 --> 00:10:07,567
But if you want to see my horns
and tail too, go ahead!

180
00:10:07,700 --> 00:10:08,833
- Sis...
- So...

181
00:10:08,967 --> 00:10:10,500
stay away from my husband!

182
00:10:10,633 --> 00:10:14,133
You may be married to my dad,
but you don't own him!

183
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:15,733
Didn't you just trap him
into marriage?

184
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:17,000
Mommy, stop it, please!

185
00:10:17,133 --> 00:10:18,867
Aren't you tired of fighting?

186
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,967
- No!
- Mommy!

187
00:10:20,100 --> 00:10:22,233
As long as there's a pest
destroying this family,

188
00:10:22,367 --> 00:10:24,100
I'll never get tired
of fighting!

189
00:10:25,467 --> 00:10:27,600
Mom, are you really going
to the hospital?

190
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:31,000
Yes. I can't let Hazel
get away with this.

191
00:10:31,133 --> 00:10:33,033
If she wants a fight,
she'll deal with me,

192
00:10:33,167 --> 00:10:34,367
not my children.

193
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:35,367
Mom, I'll go with you.

194
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:36,667
Me too, Mom.

195
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,433
No, Dear

196
00:10:38,567 --> 00:10:40,600
I don't want you caught
in the mess.

197
00:10:40,733 --> 00:10:42,533
If Hazel sees you,

198
00:10:42,667 --> 00:10:44,333
she'll target you again
because of what happened

199
00:10:44,467 --> 00:10:45,600
between you and Jessica.

200
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:48,967
But, Mom, I just want
to see Dad.

201
00:10:50,367 --> 00:10:51,433
No, Dear, don't.

202
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:54,367
Not now, wait until
your father wakes up.

203
00:10:55,433 --> 00:10:56,967
We have to go.

204
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:58,500
Let's go, Mom.

205
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:06,167
Enough!

206
00:11:06,300 --> 00:11:07,567
I won't stop!
Do you hear me?

207
00:11:07,700 --> 00:11:08,633
I won't stop!

208
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,967
I have a right to my father!

209
00:11:11,100 --> 00:11:13,667
Ever since Manuel signed
that marriage certificate,

210
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:16,167
you lost all your rights to him!

211
00:11:16,300 --> 00:11:18,500
We'll never lose
our right to our dad!

212
00:11:18,633 --> 00:11:19,700
That's not going to happen!

213
00:11:21,667 --> 00:11:22,933
Sis!

214
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:26,233
Mom!

215
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:28,433
Sis!

216
00:11:29,933 --> 00:11:30,900
Sis!

217
00:11:31,033 --> 00:11:32,100
Let's go, Jessica!

218
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:34,033
No, no!
Andrea!

219
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:35,267
- Jessica!
- Sis!

220
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,333
- Sis!
- I said let's go!

221
00:11:37,467 --> 00:11:38,333
Let's go!

222
00:11:38,467 --> 00:11:40,200
Mom!

223
00:11:40,333 --> 00:11:41,900
Jessica!

224
00:11:43,067 --> 00:11:44,333
- Sis!
- Jessica!

225
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:53,500
X-ray is clear.

226
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:55,867
No fracture, no dislocation.

227
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:59,100
So there's no need
for a cast or bandage.

228
00:11:59,233 --> 00:12:02,433
Cold compress and pain reliever
if it starts to hurt.

229
00:12:02,567 --> 00:12:05,500
And don't use it
for lifting, okay?

230
00:12:05,633 --> 00:12:07,000
Okay, Doc, thank you.

231
00:12:07,133 --> 00:12:08,300
Okay.

232
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:13,033
Was this because
of your mom, Jessica?

233
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:16,633
Yes, Auntie.

234
00:12:16,767 --> 00:12:19,233
She pushed her down the stairs.

235
00:12:19,367 --> 00:12:21,967
I'm sorry, I couldn't stop her.

236
00:12:25,533 --> 00:12:27,533
It's not your fault, Jessica.

237
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:30,467
But me...

238
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,867
I wronged you.

239
00:12:34,567 --> 00:12:37,067
I let my anger drag you
into this.

240
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,700
I hurt you.

241
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:42,667
I'm sorry.

242
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:45,533
That's over now.

243
00:12:45,667 --> 00:12:47,700
Let's forget about it.

244
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:49,300
Thank you.

245
00:12:52,733 --> 00:12:53,867
- Andrea?
- Andrea?

246
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,033
Dear.

247
00:12:56,233 --> 00:12:57,933
Is that what Hazel did to you?

248
00:12:58,433 --> 00:12:59,600
Huh?

249
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:01,933
Where is she?

250
00:13:03,167 --> 00:13:05,100
Where's your friend?

251
00:13:13,733 --> 00:13:15,567
The nerve of her to pick
a fight with me.

252
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:19,033
I shoved her.

253
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:23,233
She almost fell down the stairs.

254
00:13:24,667 --> 00:13:25,900
Serves her right.

255
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:36,000
If you were awake, you'd ask...

256
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,600
why I did it?

257
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:42,967
You'd side with that brat
of yours.

258
00:13:44,900 --> 00:13:46,633
You'd still say I'm the one
in the wrong.

259
00:13:47,567 --> 00:13:48,833
I'm aggressive.

260
00:13:51,033 --> 00:13:52,600
Get mad if you want.

261
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:58,300
The important thing
is I avenged you.

262
00:14:02,233 --> 00:14:03,500
Manuel...

263
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:07,867
Your illegitimate family's
gone too far.

264
00:14:09,533 --> 00:14:11,300
They're so entitled.

265
00:14:14,567 --> 00:14:16,033
Look what happened to you
because of them.

266
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:21,133
This is your scammer
daughter's fault.

267
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:26,633
All those illegal
schemes she gets

268
00:14:26,767 --> 00:14:29,400
into dragged you into this.

269
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:38,267
Manuel...

270
00:14:40,467 --> 00:14:41,867
Don't worry, okay?

271
00:14:44,033 --> 00:14:45,700
They won't hurt you anymore.

272
00:14:47,633 --> 00:14:50,367
I won't let them
take you from me.

273
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:52,667
Do you hear me, Manuel?

274
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,300
Huh?

275
00:15:18,533 --> 00:15:20,067
What's Alice's problem?

276
00:15:22,233 --> 00:15:23,367
Manuel...

277
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:24,667
I'm stepping out
for a bit.

278
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:31,733
Why?

279
00:15:31,867 --> 00:15:33,000
Hazel, we have a problem.

280
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:35,133
I mean, you have a problem.

281
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,167
What?

282
00:15:36,300 --> 00:15:37,900
What you did to Andrea.

283
00:15:39,067 --> 00:15:40,033
That?

284
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:41,467
Why? What happened to her?

285
00:15:41,600 --> 00:15:43,267
Is the injury bad?
Is she dead?

286
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:44,267
No, right?

287
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:45,767
I'm sure it's just
a hand sprain.

288
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:49,733
Yes, but Felma came storming in,
furious, looking for you.

289
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:53,767
That woman is so overdramatic,

290
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:54,800
always so extra!

291
00:15:54,933 --> 00:15:55,900
Why?

292
00:15:56,033 --> 00:15:57,933
Didn't her daughter
do something to mine, too?

293
00:15:58,067 --> 00:16:00,067
her "sisig girl" daugther,
do something to my daugther.

294
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:01,900
We're even then.

295
00:16:02,033 --> 00:16:03,733
Why didn't she look for me?
Where is she?

296
00:16:03,867 --> 00:16:05,967
Was she stupid enough to get
lost in the hospital?

297
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:08,433
But she found something else.

298
00:16:09,767 --> 00:16:10,633
What?

299
00:16:10,767 --> 00:16:12,767
Not what, who.

300
00:16:16,633 --> 00:16:18,533
In this hospital...

301
00:16:18,667 --> 00:16:21,033
the nurse, hurt my child.

302
00:16:22,667 --> 00:16:23,700
Mom, calm down.

303
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,733
How can I calm down?

304
00:16:26,867 --> 00:16:28,833
Didn't you see what happened
to your sister?

305
00:16:33,767 --> 00:16:35,800
Do you want me to post this
on social media?

306
00:16:37,233 --> 00:16:38,833
Don't test me.

307
00:16:38,967 --> 00:16:40,633
Wait a minute, Ms. Ruiz.

308
00:16:40,767 --> 00:16:44,100
Let me look into this
myself, okay?

309
00:16:44,267 --> 00:16:47,000
We'll conduct an investigation.

310
00:16:47,133 --> 00:16:48,500
Investigation?

311
00:16:49,600 --> 00:16:52,267
Your nurse pushed my daughter
down the stairs!

312
00:16:54,267 --> 00:16:56,133
Even her own daughter said so!

313
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,167
Jessica, sweetheart.

314
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:01,633
I'm sorry...

315
00:17:02,667 --> 00:17:04,300
you got dragged into this.

316
00:17:07,533 --> 00:17:09,467
She's lucky she didn't fall.

317
00:17:09,600 --> 00:17:10,800
What if she had?

318
00:17:11,833 --> 00:17:13,300
Would you take responsibility?

319
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,333
Nurse Miles, I'm sorry.

320
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:19,567
I just can't control
my anger right now.

321
00:17:20,633 --> 00:17:23,700
You're accountable
for what Hazel did.

322
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:25,300
She works here.

323
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,267
Do something about it!

324
00:17:29,033 --> 00:17:31,000
Suspend her!

325
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:33,267
Fire her!

326
00:17:33,400 --> 00:17:34,767
If not...

327
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,300
I'll sue her...

328
00:17:38,067 --> 00:17:40,033
and this hospital.

329
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:43,533
Wait, please, Ms. Ruiz.

330
00:17:45,033 --> 00:17:46,367
Please keep calm, okay?

331
00:17:46,500 --> 00:17:48,667
Let me fix this, okay?
Just give me a moment.

332
00:17:48,833 --> 00:17:50,900
Please wait,
give me a minute.

333
00:17:55,133 --> 00:17:57,067
Hello? Where are you?

334
00:17:58,933 --> 00:18:00,367
We need to talk.

335
00:18:14,700 --> 00:18:15,767
Hazel.

336
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,933
Hazel, what is this?

337
00:18:20,067 --> 00:18:21,867
This is conduct unbecoming.

338
00:18:22,033 --> 00:18:24,633
Weren't you already warned,
and you still didn't listen?

339
00:18:24,767 --> 00:18:26,833
But she started it first.

340
00:18:26,967 --> 00:18:28,300
What was I supposed to do?

341
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:29,767
I can't just stay quiet, can I?

342
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:32,367
This isn't about you, huh?

343
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:35,533
I don't care who you
pick fights with.

344
00:18:35,667 --> 00:18:36,967
Anywhere!

345
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:39,700
Just not here in the hospital!

346
00:18:39,833 --> 00:18:42,400
Do you know Ms. Ruiz
is threatening to sue?

347
00:18:42,533 --> 00:18:44,167
Then I'll deal with her.

348
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:47,400
Hello? She's not just suing you.

349
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:49,167
She's suing the hospital, too.

350
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:51,867
The hospital is getting dragged
into it because of you.

351
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:52,967
You're already a liability.

352
00:18:53,100 --> 00:18:55,033
Go make amends
with Ms. Ruiz. Now.

353
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:57,500
What? No!

354
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,167
You're still going
to be stubborn?

355
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:03,700
I'm telling you, if the hospital
is dragged into this

356
00:19:03,833 --> 00:19:06,467
because of your bad behavior,

357
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:09,233
I will fire you
and I will make sure

358
00:19:09,367 --> 00:19:12,400
no other hospital will take you.

359
00:19:12,533 --> 00:19:13,433
Miles.

360
00:19:13,567 --> 00:19:14,633
please don't.

361
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:21,500
I'm sorry, I only did it to
protect myself.

362
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,633
You know what I've been
through, right?

363
00:19:25,767 --> 00:19:27,433
My husband was taken from me.

364
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:30,467
I didn't...

365
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,667
That's enough.

366
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,300
Cut this drama.

367
00:19:34,433 --> 00:19:36,467
You've used that excuse before.

368
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:39,533
You want to keep this job, huh?

369
00:19:39,667 --> 00:19:41,367
Then you better obey me.

370
00:19:54,233 --> 00:19:55,867
Nurse Hazel...

371
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:58,100
you do have something
to say, right?

372
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,033
I'm sorry.

373
00:20:07,167 --> 00:20:10,000
I didn't mean to push
your daughter.

374
00:20:11,033 --> 00:20:12,567
Things just got heated.

375
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:14,800
So please...

376
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:18,467
drop the complaint.

377
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:23,833
Okay.

378
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:27,233
I won't press charges...

379
00:20:29,367 --> 00:20:31,133
on one condition.

380
00:20:33,833 --> 00:20:35,167
I knew it.

381
00:20:36,233 --> 00:20:37,233
What condition?

382
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:40,533
To get near Manuel, right?

383
00:20:40,667 --> 00:20:41,700
- Hazel!
- I'm right, aren't I?

384
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:44,033
Hazel, please stop,
come on!

385
00:20:44,167 --> 00:20:45,167
No!

386
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:47,533
Can't you hear her?

387
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:49,600
She's trying to trick us!

388
00:20:50,933 --> 00:20:52,467
I'm right, aren't I?

389
00:20:54,633 --> 00:20:56,533
Yes.

390
00:20:56,667 --> 00:20:59,167
I'm not filing a case,

391
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:04,367
but let me
and my kids see Manuel.

392
00:21:05,433 --> 00:21:06,800
No!

393
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,633
I won't allow it!

394
00:21:11,233 --> 00:21:12,233
You shameless woman.

395
00:21:12,367 --> 00:21:14,133
You've got some nerve!

396
00:21:16,233 --> 00:21:18,133
Is that so?

397
00:21:18,267 --> 00:21:20,133
Fine, I'm easy to deal with.

398
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,600
I'll go ahead.

399
00:21:24,733 --> 00:21:26,533
You'll hear from my lawyer.

400
00:21:26,667 --> 00:21:27,733
Ma'am.

401
00:21:27,867 --> 00:21:29,233
Hazel!

402
00:21:29,367 --> 00:21:30,833
Wait.

403
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,467
Fine.

404
00:21:41,533 --> 00:21:44,300
I'll let you see Manuel.

405
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:48,467
But clear my name with my boss.

406
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:51,900
Yes, your daughter and I fought,

407
00:21:52,033 --> 00:21:53,633
but I didn't mean to push her.

408
00:21:53,767 --> 00:21:55,400
It was an accident.

409
00:22:01,133 --> 00:22:02,267
Nurse Miles...

410
00:22:04,033 --> 00:22:06,500
I accept that
it was just an accident.

411
00:22:06,633 --> 00:22:09,233
that Hazel pushing my daughter.

412
00:22:09,367 --> 00:22:11,333
I'm no longer pressing charges.

413
00:22:17,333 --> 00:22:19,233
Thank you, Ma'am.

414
00:22:40,733 --> 00:22:42,000
Manuel.

415
00:22:43,833 --> 00:22:45,700
Manuel, don't give up.

416
00:22:49,400 --> 00:22:52,033
You still haven't talked things
out with Andrea.

417
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,533
Your Andeng.

418
00:22:56,567 --> 00:22:58,233
She's waiting for you.

419
00:22:59,767 --> 00:23:06,800
And Jeff, you two haven't
properly bonded yet.

420
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,267
You still owe me promises.

421
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:13,800
I'm counting on you...

422
00:23:15,300 --> 00:23:20,100
to speed up the annulment
from Hazel.

423
00:23:21,167 --> 00:23:25,933
I'll go to any length,
even fight her,

424
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:30,567
to stop her from blocking
my love for you.

425
00:23:33,733 --> 00:23:37,900
Like I said,
I'll fix everything.

426
00:23:39,233 --> 00:23:40,867
I will fight for this.

427
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:45,967
I have so many plans for us.

428
00:23:48,067 --> 00:23:52,600
Dreams and promises I will keep.

429
00:23:56,067 --> 00:24:00,167
I'll try to put our family
back together.

430
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:01,967
Thank you, Auntie Felma.

431
00:24:03,267 --> 00:24:05,800
Once the kids forgive me,

432
00:24:06,767 --> 00:24:10,800
I'll bring back the joy, peace,

433
00:24:11,833 --> 00:24:14,700
and warmth we once had.

434
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:18,433
I'll recover, Felma.

435
00:24:20,067 --> 00:24:26,033
I'll do everything
to walk again.

436
00:24:27,700 --> 00:24:28,833
Because I dream of...

437
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:39,467
I can walk you down the aisle
not in a wheelchair.

438
00:24:42,933 --> 00:24:45,300
Get well soon, okay?

439
00:24:46,533 --> 00:24:51,900
Be strong,

440
00:24:52,033 --> 00:24:56,100
so we can finally annul
your marriage to Hazel.

441
00:25:02,067 --> 00:25:03,600
I'll take you back...

442
00:25:05,933 --> 00:25:08,767
from the woman
who stole you from me.

443
00:25:25,233 --> 00:25:27,567
She's even whispering
to my husband.

444
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:30,033
So the lawsuit
was just her leverage.

445
00:25:30,167 --> 00:25:31,600
That's also your fault, Mom.

446
00:25:31,733 --> 00:25:33,533
You hurt Big Sister Andrea.

447
00:25:33,667 --> 00:25:35,333
Call her big sister
one more time,

448
00:25:35,500 --> 00:25:37,600
and I'll make sure she knows
exactly who you are.

449
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:39,433
Jeff was right.

450
00:25:39,567 --> 00:25:41,400
She really is Satan's sister.

451
00:25:41,533 --> 00:25:43,467
Such an evil woman.

452
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:44,867
Poor Jessica.

453
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:46,867
Of all the moms
she could've had,

454
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:48,100
it had to be Hazel.

455
00:25:48,233 --> 00:25:50,000
Good thing she takes after Dad.

456
00:25:50,133 --> 00:25:51,400
We're not sure about that.

457
00:25:51,533 --> 00:25:53,933
I thought you were just getting
Dad's papers?

458
00:25:54,067 --> 00:25:56,300
Why are you packing up
his things?

459
00:25:56,433 --> 00:25:57,933
Because once Dad gets out
of the hospital,

460
00:25:58,067 --> 00:25:59,767
we're moving into the apartment.

461
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:02,133
You really take after your mom.

462
00:26:02,267 --> 00:26:03,833
You're just as mean as she is!

463
00:26:03,967 --> 00:26:05,733
You're worse, Coleen!

464
00:26:05,867 --> 00:26:08,533
You're always hurting me!
Always picking fights!

465
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:10,367
Go on then, hurt me!

466
00:26:10,500 --> 00:26:11,800
Do your worst, Coleen!

467
00:26:11,933 --> 00:26:13,533
Because it will be your last.

468
00:26:13,667 --> 00:26:16,967
I will fight for my right
as Dad's legal daughter

469
00:26:17,100 --> 00:26:18,267
from now on, Coleen.

470
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:21,467
You won't get near him again.
You won't visit him ever again.
